      • isDefaultValue

        public boolean isDefaultValue(IWriteContext context)
        Determines whether in the current context, the value is the default value and therefore no data element needs to be written.

        This implementation will return false if no default has been set. Otherwise it will use getValue(IWriteContext, Object) and compare the result with the DefaultValue to determine whether they are equal and therefore no data needs to be written.

        Specified by:
        isDefaultValue in interface IOutputHandler
        Parameters:
        context - The context.
        Returns:
        true if for the current context the default value applies and therefore no data element needs to be written.

        public final void setKeyDefinitionScope(KeyScope scope)
        Sets the scope for the key definition.

        Note that the official GraphML schema does not support the KeyScope.GRAPHML so this implementation will silently ignore this which will result in KeyScope.ALL implicitly being defined.

        Parameters:

      • writeKeyDefinitionContent

        public void writeKeyDefinitionContent(IWriteContext context)
                               throws IOException
        Writes the contents of the key definition.

        Depending on whether KeyDefaultWritingEnabled is enabled and DefaultExisting is true, this method will write the GraphML 'default' element and use writeValueCore(IWriteContext, Object) to serialize the DefaultValue.

        Specified by:
        writeKeyDefinitionContent in interface IOutputHandler
        Throws:
        IOException - If the key definition cannot be written.
        Parameters:
        context - The context.

      • writeValue

        public final void writeValue(IWriteContext context)
                      throws IOException
        Actually writes the value for the current context.

        This method will use getValue(IWriteContext, Object) to obtain the data and delegate to writeValueCore(IWriteContext, Object) to perform the actual serialization.

        Specified by:
        writeValue in interface IOutputHandler
        Throws:
        IOException - If the value cannot be written.
        Parameters:
        context - The context.
